### Government

The city operates under the governance structure of a [Metropolitan borough](/Metropolitan_borough), with its affairs managed by the [Coventry City Council](/Coventry_City_Council). The leadership adheres to a [Leader and cabinet](/Local_Government_Act_2000) model. Currently, the esteemed [Lord Mayor](/List_of_mayors_of_Coventry) is Mal Mutton, a figurehead whose importance is, one assumes, paramount to civic pride. The [Council Leader](/Leader_of_the_Council) is George Duggins, representing the [Labour Party](/Labour_Party_(UK)), navigating the labyrinthine corridors of local power. Julie Nugent occupies the role of [Chief Executive](/Chief_executive_(head_of_government)), ensuring the machinery of bureaucracy continues its tireless churn. At the national level, Coventry is represented by three [MPs](/List_of_MPs_elected_in_the_2024_United_Kingdom_general_election): [Mary Creagh](/Mary_Creagh) ([L](/Labour_Party_(UK))), [Taiwo Owatemi](/Taiwo_Owatemi) ([L](/Labour_Party_(UK))), and [Zarah Sultana](/Zarah_Sultana) ([Ind](/Independent_politician)). A diverse collection of voices, though whether they sing in harmony is another matter entirely.

### Area

The designated area for the [City](/City_status_in_the_United_Kingdom) and [metropolitan borough](/Metropolitan_borough) spans approximately 38.09&#160;sq&#160;mi (98.64&#160;km 2 ). A modest patch of earth, for all its historical drama.

