As of 2021, the [City](/City_status_in_the_United_Kingdom) and [metropolitan borough](/Metropolitan_borough) recorded a population of 345,324 souls, each presumably with their own intricate, often tedious, lives. This translates to a density of 11,400 individuals per square mile (4,390/km 2 ). The broader [Metro](/Metropolitan_area) area, a more expansive definition of human clustering, registers 651,600 residents. Those who reside here are known as [Coventrians](/Demonym) or, less commonly, Coventarians.

